          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.4;"><strong>🇺🇦 Ukraine:</strong>   
          Ukrainian President Volodymyr Zelensky has <a href="https://www.bbc.com/news/articles/cn8g8ylvyldo" target="_blank">proposed</a> that NATO membership should include all of Ukraine, even territories currently under Russian control, to ensure security and end the war. In an interview with Sky News, he stated that Ukraine could seek to reclaim these areas diplomatically if NATO membership was offered for its internationally recognized borders. Zelensky rejected limiting NATO membership to only parts of Ukraine, as it would validate Russian claims to other regions. Although discussions about a "<a href="https://kyivindependent.com/as-signs-of-talks-about-west-germany-model-for-ukraine-peace-emerge-experts-weigh-in-on-feasibility/" target="_blank">West Germany model</a>" of partial membership exist, no formal offers have been made, and NATO involvement seems unlikely.</p>
        </mj-text>
